<br>
im familiar with muds on a fairly basic level, so you dont have to dumb it down too far.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uglipthegnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glip the Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pantsless Asst. Administrator</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/8/02 8:24:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7068.topic&index=18>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.keithparkinson.com/glip2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Muds with no downtime?</span><hr size=1> The DragonRealms combat system is the best because its completely balanced, realistic, and extremely customizable.<br>
<br>
<br>
Simply put:<br>
<br>
- Anybody can learn any weapon or wear any armor.   But a mage wearing plate and using a two handed sword is going to have trouble casting his spells unless he's really good at what he's doing.  <br>
<br>
- You CAN &quot;work off&quot; the armor and heavy weapons as a mage, it just takes a lot of work, and not many people do it because it makes more sense to wear lighter armor since  it allows more unhindered movement.  Same goes for theives.<br>
<br>
- Weapon categories are broken up into:<br>
Light Edged (daggers, knives etc..)<br>
Medium Edged (rapiers, scimitars, cutlasses etc..)<br>
Heavy Edged (broadsword, longsword, battle axe etc..)<br>
Two Handed Edged (two handed sword, two handed battle axe..)<br>
<br>
Light Blunt (hatchet etc..) <br>
Medium Blunt (cudgel etc..)<br>
Heavy Blunt (heavy mace, morning star etc..)<br>
Two Handed Blunt (flail etc..)<br>
<br>
Light Thrown (throwing daggers, bola)<br>
Heavy Thrown (spears)<br>
<br>
Short Bow<br>
Composite Bow<br>
Long Bow<br>
<br>
Light Crossbow<br>
Heavy Crossbow<br>
<br>
Polearm<br>
and probably a few others I'm forgetting.<br>
<br>
There's also similar skills for things like:<br>
<br>
Your armor type (leather, light plate, heavy plate, light chain, heavy chain etc..)<br>
<br>
Evasion<br>
<br>
Dodging<br>
<br>
Shield Usage<br>
<br>
etc..<br>
<br>
The combat system isn't leveled based, so you can learn as much of that stuff as you want (time consuming if you don't level though) at any level.  You go up in &quot;ranks&quot; as you get better.  You get better by either having someone teach you or using the skill.<br>
<br>
<br>
Anyway, all of your combat skills go into determining how well you do in a fight.  And during the fight you'll have to parry, dodge, evade and attack in a variety of manners.<br>
<br>
I need to go to class now, but I can add on this during lunch when I get home. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uphantomrogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phantom Rogue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/8/02 9:27:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7068.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Muds with no downtime?</span><hr size=1> OMG GLip!<br>
